  "summary": {
    "as": "Introduced in House",
    "asOf": "2004-03-25",
    "date": "2004-04-20T14:20:29Z",
    "text": "Firearm Commerce Modernization Act - Amends the Brady Handgun Violence Prevention Act to permit a licensed importer, manufacturer, dealer, or collector to: (1) sell or deliver a firearm (currently, a rifle or shotgun) to a resident of a State other than a State in which the licensee's place of business is located or temporarily located if the transferee meets in person with the transferor to accomplish the transfer; and (2) conduct business temporarily at any gun show or event sponsored by any national, State, or local organization, or any affiliate devoted to the collection, competitive use, or other sporting use of firearms (currently, only at such a location in the State specified on the person's license).\n\nProvides that nothing in the Act shall be construed to diminish the right of a licensee to conduct firearms transfers (currently, \"curious or relics\" firearms transfers) with another licensee away from the transferor's business premises."
  },
